# 🧠 BrainUp – AI CRM Enrichment

> Automatically enrich CRM records with company websites, business insights and personalized outreach angles using AI.

---

# Why I Built This

During B2B prospecting, I noticed that most CRM records were incomplete.

Typical missing information included:

- Company website
- Business context
- Prospecting notes
- Personalized outreach angles

Without this information, every sales email required manual research before being written.

I built this workflow to eliminate that repetitive work.

Instead of spending several minutes researching every company, the CRM enriches itself automatically.

---

# The Problem

Prospecting quality depends on data quality.

Unfortunately, CRM databases quickly become inconsistent:

- Missing websites
- Empty notes
- No business context
- Generic outreach messages

Sales teams spend valuable time searching Google instead of speaking with prospects.

---

# The Solution

This workflow automatically enriches CRM records by combining:

- Hunter.io
- Website scraping
- GPT-4.1
- Airtable
- n8n

The result is a CRM containing richer and more actionable information for every prospect.

---

# Workflow Overview

```
Schedule
    │
    ▼
Read incomplete CRM records
    │
    ▼
Find company website
(Hunter)
    │
    ▼
Fallback to email domain
    │
    ▼
Scrape website
    │
    ▼
Extract website content
    │
    ▼
GPT generates:
• Business Notes
• Outreach Angles
    │
    ▼
Update Airtable
```

---

# How It Works

## 1. Read CRM

The workflow retrieves every company whose CRM record is incomplete.

Missing fields include:

- Website
- Notes
- Prospecting Angles

---

## 2. Website Discovery

If the website is missing:

Priority 1

- Hunter Domain Search

Priority 2

- Email domain extraction

This significantly increases the number of usable CRM records.

---

## 3. Website Analysis

If a website is found:

- HTML is downloaded
- Scripts removed
- Useful text extracted
- Business signals identified

Examples:

- Property valuation
- Rental management
- Luxury real estate
- Multiple agencies
- Investment
- Contact forms

---

## 4. AI Enrichment

GPT receives:

- company name
- website
- extracted text
- detected business signals

The model generates two CRM fields:

### Notes

Business summary including:

- estimated company profile
- services
- target customers
- likely challenges

### Outreach Angles

Personalized sales angles including:

- probable pain points
- conversation starters
- email hook

---

## 5. CRM Update

Only missing fields are updated.

Existing information is never overwritten.

---

# Technologies

- n8n
- Airtable
- Hunter.io API
- OpenAI GPT-4.1 Mini
- JavaScript
- HTTP Requests

---

# Business Benefits

This automation:

- reduces manual prospect research
- improves CRM quality
- increases personalization
- prepares better cold emails
- standardizes prospect information

Instead of researching every company manually, sales teams receive enriched records ready for outreach.

---

# Why AI?

AI is particularly effective here because every company is different.

Traditional rules cannot summarize thousands of websites into useful sales insights.

GPT transforms raw website content into structured business intelligence.

---

# Current Limitations

This workflow intentionally does NOT:

- verify whether generated insights are 100% correct;
- detect company changes over time;
- enrich social media profiles;
- search LinkedIn;
- enrich phone numbers;
- scrape JavaScript-heavy websites;
- replace human validation.

AI suggestions should always be reviewed before being used in sales conversations.

---

# Future Improvements

Planned improvements:

- LinkedIn enrichment
- Google Maps data
- Company size estimation
- Industry classification
- CRM scoring
- Competitor detection
- Automatic company summaries
- Multi-language support


# Business Impact

By enriching CRM records automatically, sales teams spend less time researching companies and more time speaking with qualified prospects.

The objective is not to replace prospect research completely.

It is to automate the repetitive part while preserving human judgment for high-value interactions.

